<subSubSection pageId="495" pageNumber="496" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="495" pageNumber="496">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Letzner" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Poecilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="495" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">Poecilus bicolor</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1846b: 232 [secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="495" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="495" pageNumber="496">Pterostichus bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Aragona, 1830)]. Type locality: &quot;ad Rocky Mountains&quot; (original citation). One syntype in MCZ [# 5640]. Note. LeConte (1853a: 255) stated that he had a single specimen of this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="495" pageNumber="496">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Csiki" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="495" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coloradensis">Pterostichus coloradensis</taxonomicName>
Csiki, 1930: 591. Replacement name for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="495" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="495" pageNumber="496">Pterostichus bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(LeConte, 1846).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="495" pageNumber="496" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="495" pageNumber="496">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="495" pageNumber="496">This species is known for sure only from the syntype. The records from northeastern Kansas (Horn 1872c: 385; Popenoe 1878: 78) are suspect.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="495" pageNumber="496" type="records">
<paragraph pageId="495" pageNumber="496">Records.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="495" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="495" pageNumber="496">USA</emphasis>
: [CO, KS]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="495" pageNumber="496" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="495" pageNumber="496">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="495" pageNumber="496">
Adults of this species are structurally similar to, and possibly conspecific with, those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Poecilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="495" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucublandus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="495" pageNumber="496">Poecilus lucublandus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say as defined by Lindroth (1966: 482-483).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
